    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I don't have an use case for the exposed `render`, even if I see some possible benefits (custom delimiters, dynamic attribute without modifying the root object, etc.) but I believe we should stick with the spec.\n\nAbout the binding however, I'm using it in mutliple Shopify helpers. It might not be a \"best-practice\", since this means I'm doing some assertions on how the object is structured, but my best example is a \"discount\" percentage, that I'm calculating based on two attributes, and something like\n\n``` hogan\n{{# helpers.discount }}{{/ helpers.discount }}\n```\n\nis way more elegant than\n\n``` hogan\n{{# helpers.discount }}{{ price }} | {{ discounted_price }}{{/ helpers.discount }}\n```\n\nwith a regex in the lambda to split the parameters + parsing from string to number.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-10-05T03:08:48Z",
